# 6. Post-login controller

## `PostLoginController.java`

```java
package com.example.app.auth.controller;

import com.example.app.auth.dto.HandoffExchangeResponse;
import com.example.app.auth.service.PostLoginService;
import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;
import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;
import lombok.RequiredArgsConstructor;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestParam;

import java.io.IOException;

@Controller
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class PostLoginController {

    private final PostLoginService postLoginService;

    @GetMapping("/post-login")
    public void postLogin(
            @RequestParam("code") String code,
            HttpServletRequest request,
            HttpServletResponse response
    ) throws IOException {

        HandoffExchangeResponse login = postLoginService.loginWithHandoffCode(code, request);

        response.sendRedirect("/home");
    }
}
```

You can later redirect based on `login.getAppId()` or user role.

